<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11455] Automatic transform String to DBObject after previous conversion error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11455</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i found a bug. To reproduce it you can execute the code (see attachment file).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The bug is simple:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After an invalid conversion, the automatic String -&amp;gt; JSON transformation used to put a document into MongoDB collection, fail!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Application flow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;First document can be convert to JSON, Mongodb create a document (correct)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Second document has an error, Mongodb cannot create a document (correct)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Third document can be convert to JSON but Mongodb cannot create a document into collection because automatic conversion is broken!!!  (BUG)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Kings regards&lt;/p&gt;</description>
